p: If no obvious adhesion was found during the second hysteroscopic inspection, an embryo transfer (ET) or spontaneous pregnancy was planned for these patients. Among them, three patients became pregnant after ET (Patient Nos. 10, 17, and 18), seven patients became pregnant spontaneously (Patient Nos. 1, 4, 5, 15, 19, 20, and 23), and two patients experienced failed ET (Patient Nos. 3 and 16) (Table 1).
